# ORVIX Product Rules

## Source of truth

Before major UI, UX, or frontend architecture work, read `/docs/orvix/` (start with README.md).

## Product identity

- ORVIX is an **operations platform for business events** — not a CRM, not a connector dashboard.
- Core cycle: **Connect → Understand → Decide → Deliver → Observe**.
- No features without product rationale. No decoration without function.

## Design language

- Premium B2B SaaS: calm, minimal, typography-first (Linear / Stripe direction).
- Tokens: background `#FAFAFA`, text `#171717`, border `#E8E8E8`, accent `#5E6AD2` (sparingly).
- **No** glassmorphism, decorative gradients, or heavy shadows on surfaces.
- Use `.type-display|title|body|caption|label`, `.surface`, `.nav-item-active`, `.hairline-b`.
- Status: `StatusBadge` (dot + text). KPIs: `KpiCard` minimal mode or divided surfaces.

## Architecture

- `components/ui/` — primitives only; extend, do not duplicate.
- `components/layout/` — app shell (sidebar, header, footer).
- Feature UI in `components/<feature>/`; `app/` pages are thin composition layers.
- No inline styles. No new colors without updating `globals.css` + `docs/orvix/05_design_system.md`.

## Prohibited without explicit request

- Prisma / API / auth / integration logic changes in design-only tasks.
- New components that mirror existing ui primitives (`button-v2`, `metric-card`, etc.).

## Quality before done

```bash
npm run build
npm run lint
```

Report: what changed, files touched, checks passed, docs updated.
